msgid ""
msgstr "Monks’ Relinquishment"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:pts-cs0.6"
msgid "8. Upakkhaṭasikkhāpada"
msgstr "8. The training rule on what is set aside"

#. </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:pts-cs1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Origin story"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="1"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-np.8.1"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.53"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2015"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:pts-cs1.1"
msgid ""
"Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa "
"ārāme."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, "
"Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:pts-cs1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena aññataro puriso pajāpatiṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "At that time a certain man said to his wife,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:pts-cs1.3"
msgid "“ayyaṃ upanandaṃ cīvarena acchādessāmī”ti."
msgstr "“I’ll give a robe to Venerable Upananda.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:pts-cs1.4"
msgid ""
"Assosi kho aññataro piṇḍacāriko bhikkhu tassa purisassa imaṃ vācaṃ "
"bhāsamānassa."
msgstr "A monk who was an alms-collector heard that man making that statement."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:pts-cs1.5"
msgid "Atha kho so bhikkhu yenāyasmā upanando sakyaputto tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "He then went to Upananda"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:pts-cs1.6"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ upanandaṃ sakyaputtaṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "and said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:pts-cs1.7"
msgid "“mahāpuññosi tvaṃ, āvuso upananda."
msgstr "“Upananda, you have much merit."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:pts-cs1.8"
msgid "Amukasmiṃ okāse aññataro puriso pajāpatiṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "I’ve just heard a man telling his wife"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:pts-cs1.9"
msgid "‘ayyaṃ upanandaṃ cīvarena acchādessāmī’”ti."
msgstr "that he’ll give you a robe.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:pts-cs1.10"
msgid "“Atthāvuso, maṃ so upaṭṭhāko”ti."
msgstr "“He’s my supporter.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2016"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:pts-cs1.11"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā upanando sakyaputto yena so puriso tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "Upananda then went to that man"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:pts-cs1.12"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā taṃ purisaṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "and said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:pts-cs1.13"
msgid "“saccaṃ kira maṃ tvaṃ, āvuso, cīvarena acchādetukāmosī”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it true that you desire to give me a robe?”"

#. </p><p>
#. VAR: meyya → mayya (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:pts-cs1.14"
msgid "“Api meyya, evaṃ hoti—"
msgstr "“Indeed,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:pts-cs1.15"
msgid "‘ayyaṃ upanandaṃ cīvarena acchādessāmī’”ti."
msgstr "that’s just what I was thinking.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:pts-cs1.16"
msgid ""
"“Sace kho maṃ tvaṃ, āvuso, cīvarena acchādetukāmosi, evarūpena cīvarena "
"acchādehi."
msgstr "“If that’s the case, give me such-and-such a robe."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:pts-cs1.17"
msgid "Kyāhaṃ tena acchannopi karissāmi yāhaṃ na paribhuñjissāmī”ti."
msgstr "For what’s the point of giving a robe that I won’t use?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:pts-cs1.18"
msgid "Atha kho so puriso ujjhāyati khiyyati vipāceti—"
msgstr "That man grumbled and complained,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:pts-cs1.19"
msgid "“mahicchā ime samaṇā sakyaputtiyā asantuṭṭhā."
msgstr "“These Sakyan ascetics have great desires; they are not content."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:pts-cs1.20"
msgid "Nayime sukarā cīvarena acchādetuṃ."
msgstr "It’s no easy matter to give them a robe."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:pts-cs1.21"
msgid ""
"Kathañhi nāma ayyo upanando mayā pubbe appavārito maṃ upasaṅkamitvā cīvare "
"vikappaṃ āpajjissatī”ti."
msgstr ""
"How can Venerable Upananda come to me and specify the kind of robe he wants "
"without first being invited by me?”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="3"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.54"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2017"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:pts-cs1.22"
msgid ""
"Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū tassa purisassa ujjhāyantassa khiyyantassa vipācentassa."
msgstr "The monks heard the complaints of that man,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:pts-cs1.23"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "and the monks of few desires …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:pts-cs1.24"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized him,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:pts-cs1.25"
msgid ""
"“kathañhi nāma āyasmā upanando sakyaputto pubbe appavārito gahapatikaṃ "
"upasaṅkamitvā cīvare vikappaṃ āpajjissatī”ti."
msgstr ""
"“How can Venerable Upananda approach a lay person and specify the kind of "
"robe he wants without first being invited?”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="4"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.216"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2018"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:pts-cs1.26"
msgid ""
"Atha kho te bhikkhū āyasmantaṃ upanandaṃ sakyaputtaṃ anekapariyāyena "
"vigarahitvā bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ … pe …"
msgstr "After criticizing him in many ways, they told the Master …"

#. VAR: gahapatikaṃ → gahapatiṃ (bj)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:pts-cs1.27"
msgid ""
"“saccaṃ kira tvaṃ, upananda, pubbe appavārito gahapatikaṃ upasaṅkamitvā "
"cīvare vikappaṃ āpajjasī”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it true, Upananda, that you acted like this?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:pts-cs1.28"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:pts-cs1.29"
msgid "“Ñātako te, upananda, aññātako”ti?"
msgstr "“Is he a relative of yours?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:pts-cs1.30"
msgid "“Aññātako, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“No, Master.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:pts-cs1.31"
msgid ""
"“Aññātako, moghapurisa, aññātakassa na jānāti patirūpaṃ vā appatirūpaṃ vā "
"santaṃ vā asantaṃ vā."
msgstr ""
"“Foolish man, people who are not related don’t know what’s appropriate and "
"what’s inappropriate in dealing with each other, what’s right and what’s "
"wrong."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:pts-cs1.32"
msgid ""
"Tattha nāma tvaṃ, moghapurisa, pubbe appavārito aññātakaṃ gahapatikaṃ "
"upasaṅkamitvā cīvare vikappaṃ āpajjissasi."
msgstr ""
"And still you went to an unrelated lay person and specified the kind of robe "
"you wanted without first being invited."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:pts-cs1.33"
msgid "Netaṃ, moghapurisa, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:pts-cs1.34"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:pts-cs1.34a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="5"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2019"></a>
#. <span class="rule"> 
#. VAR: cīvaracetāpannaṃ → cīvara­ce­tāpanaṃ (s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:pts-cs1.35"
msgid ""
"“Bhikkhuṃ paneva uddissa aññātakassa gahapatissa vā gahapatāniyā vā "
"cīvaracetāpannaṃ upakkhaṭaṃ hoti—"
msgstr ""
"‘If a layman or laywoman has set aside a robe fund for an unrelated monk, "
"thinking,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:pts-cs1.36"
msgid ""
"‘iminā cīvaracetāpannena cīvaraṃ cetāpetvā itthannāmaṃ bhikkhuṃ cīvarena "
"acchādessāmī’ti;"
msgstr "‘With this robe fund I will buy a robe and give it to monk so-and-so;’"

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.55"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:pts-cs1.37"
msgid ""
"tatra ce so bhikkhu pubbe appavārito upasaṅkamitvā cīvare vikappaṃ āpajjeyya—"
msgstr ""
"and if that monk, without first being invited, approaches them and specifies "
"the kind of robe he wants, saying,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:pts-cs1.38"
msgid ""
"‘sādhu vata maṃ āyasmā iminā cīvaracetāpannena evarūpaṃ vā evarūpaṃ vā "
"cīvaraṃ cetāpetvā acchādehī’ti,"
msgstr ""
"‘It would be good if you would use this robe fund to buy such-and-such a "
"robe and then give it to me,’"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:pts-cs1.39"
msgid "kalyāṇakamyataṃ upādāya, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr ""
"and he does so because he wants something nice, he commits and offense "
"entailing relinquishment and confession.’”"

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:pts-cs1.40"
msgid "(<em>8</em>:<strong>27</strong>)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:pts-cs2.1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="6"></a><a class="pts-cs-empty" id="bu-np.8.2"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-np.8.2.1"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2020"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:pts-cs2.1.1"
msgid "Bhikkhuṃ paneva uddissāti"
msgstr "For a […] monk:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:pts-cs2.1.2"
msgid "bhikkhussatthāya, bhikkhuṃ ārammaṇaṃ karitvā, bhikkhuṃ acchādetukāmo."
msgstr ""
"for the benefit of a monk; making a monk the object of consideration, one "
"desires to give to him."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="7"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2021"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:pts-cs2.1.3"
msgid "Aññātako nāma"
msgstr "Unrelated:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:pts-cs2.1.4"
msgid "mātito vā pitito vā yāva sattamā pitāmahayugā asambaddho."
msgstr ""
"anyone who is not a descendant of one’s male ancestors going back seven "
"generations, either on the mother’s side or on the father’s side."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="8"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2022"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:pts-cs2.1.5"
msgid "Gahapati nāma"
msgstr "A layman:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:pts-cs2.1.6"
msgid "yo koci agāraṃ ajjhāvasati."
msgstr "any man who lives in a house."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="9"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2023"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:pts-cs2.1.7"
msgid "Gahapatānī nāma"
msgstr "A laywoman:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:pts-cs2.1.8"
msgid "yā kāci agāraṃ ajjhāvasati."
msgstr "any woman who lives in a house."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="10"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2024"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:pts-cs2.1.9"
msgid "Cīvaracetāpannaṃ nāma"
msgstr "A robe fund:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:pts-cs2.1.10"
msgid ""
"hiraññaṃ vā suvaṇṇaṃ vā muttā vā maṇi vā pavāḷo vā phaliko vā paṭako vā "
"suttaṃ vā kappāso vā."
msgstr ""
"money, gold, a pearl, a gem, a coral, a crystal, cloth, thread, or cotton "
"wool."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="11"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2025"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:pts-cs2.1.11"
msgid "Iminā cīvaracetāpannenāti"
msgstr "With this robe fund:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:pts-cs2.1.12"
msgid "paccupaṭṭhitena."
msgstr "with that which is at one’s disposal."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="12"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2026"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:pts-cs2.1.13"
msgid "Cetāpetvāti"
msgstr "I will buy:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:pts-cs2.1.14"
msgid "parivattetvā."
msgstr "having exchanged."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="13"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2027"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:pts-cs2.1.15"
msgid "Acchādessāmīti"
msgstr "I will […] give:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:pts-cs2.1.16"
msgid "dassāmi."
msgstr "I will donate."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="14"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2028"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:pts-cs2.1.17"
msgid "Tatra ce so bhikkhūti"
msgstr "If that monk:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:pts-cs2.1.18"
msgid "yaṃ bhikkhuṃ uddissa cīvaracetāpannaṃ upakkhaṭaṃ hoti so bhikkhu."
msgstr "the monk for whom the robe fund has been set aside."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="15"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2029"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:pts-cs2.1.19"
msgid "Pubbe appavāritoti"
msgstr "Without first being invited:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:pts-cs2.1.20"
msgid "pubbe avutto hoti—"
msgstr "he or she has not said beforehand:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:pts-cs2.1.21"
msgid "“kīdisena te, bhante, cīvarena attho,"
msgstr "“Venerable, what kind of robe do you need?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:pts-cs2.1.22"
msgid "kīdisaṃ te cīvaraṃ cetāpemī”ti?"
msgstr "What kind of robe can I buy for you?”"

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="16"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2030"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:pts-cs2.1.23"
msgid "Upasaṅkamitvāti"
msgstr "Approaches him:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:pts-cs2.1.24"
msgid "gharaṃ gantvā yattha katthaci upasaṅkamitvā."
msgstr "having gone to his house or having gone wherever."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="17"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2031"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:pts-cs2.1.25"
msgid "Cīvare vikappaṃ āpajjeyyāti"
msgstr "Specifies the kind of robe he wants:"

#. </span><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.56"></a><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:pts-cs2.1.26"
msgid "āyataṃ vā hotu vitthataṃ vā appitaṃ vā saṇhaṃ vā."
msgstr "please make it long or wide or closely woven or soft."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="18"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.217"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2032"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:pts-cs2.1.27"
msgid "Iminā cīvaracetāpannenāti"
msgstr "This robe fund:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:pts-cs2.1.28"
msgid "paccupaṭṭhitena."
msgstr "that which is at one’s disposal."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="19"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2033"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:pts-cs2.1.29"
msgid "Evarūpaṃ vā evarūpaṃ vāti."
msgstr "Such-and-such:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:pts-cs2.1.30"
msgid "Āyataṃ vā vitthataṃ vā appitaṃ vā saṇhaṃ vā."
msgstr "long or wide or closely woven or soft."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="20"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2034"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:pts-cs2.1.31"
msgid "Cetāpetvāti"
msgstr "To buy:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:pts-cs2.1.32"
msgid "parivattetvā."
msgstr "having exchanged."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="21"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2035"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:pts-cs2.1.33"
msgid "Acchādehīti"
msgstr "Give:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:pts-cs2.1.34"
msgid "dajjehi."
msgstr "donate."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="22"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2036"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:pts-cs2.1.35"
msgid "Kalyāṇakamyataṃ upādāyāti"
msgstr "Because he wants something nice:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
#. VAR: sādhatthiko → sādhutthiko (s1-3)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:pts-cs2.1.36"
msgid "sādhatthiko mahagghatthiko."
msgstr "wanting something nice, wanting something expensive."

#. </span></p><hr><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:pts-cs2.1.37"
msgid ""
"Tassa vacanena āyataṃ vā vitthataṃ vā appitaṃ vā saṇhaṃ vā cetāpeti, payoge "
"dukkaṭaṃ."
msgstr ""
"If that lay person buys a robe that is long, wide, closely woven, or soft "
"because of the monk’s statement, then for the act of making the statement, "
"he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:pts-cs2.1.38"
msgid "Paṭilābhena nissaggiyaṃ hoti."
msgstr "When he gets the robe, it becomes subject to relinquishment."

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:pts-cs2.1.39"
msgid "Nissajjitabbaṃ saṃghassa vā gaṇassa vā puggalassa vā."
msgstr "The robe should be relinquished to an Order, a group, or an individual."

#. <span class="kamma"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:pts-cs2.1.40"
msgid "Evañca pana, bhikkhave, nissajjitabbaṃ …"
msgstr "“And, monks, it should be relinquished in this way. …"

#. <span class="pe"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:pts-cs2.1.41"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""
"To be expanded as in <a class=\"cr\" href=\"./pli-tv-bu-vb-np1#13\">"
"Relinquishment 1, paragraphs 13–17</a>, with appropriate substitutions. …"

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:pts-cs2.1.42"
msgid ""
"“idaṃ me, bhante, cīvaraṃ pubbe appavārito aññātakaṃ gahapatikaṃ "
"upasaṅkamitvā cīvare vikappaṃ āpannaṃ nissaggiyaṃ,"
msgstr ""
"‘Venerables, this robe which I received after approaching an unrelated lay "
"person and specifying the kind of robe I wanted without first being invited "
"is to be relinquished."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:pts-cs2.1.43"
msgid "imāhaṃ saṃghassa nissajjāmī”ti … pe …"
msgstr "I relinquish it to the Order.’ …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:pts-cs2.1.44"
msgid "dadeyyāti … pe …"
msgstr "the Order should give …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:pts-cs2.1.45"
msgid "dadeyyunti … pe …"
msgstr "you should give …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:pts-cs2.1.46"
msgid "āyasmato dammīti."
msgstr "‘I give this robe back to you.’”"

#. </span></p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:pts-cs2.2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="23"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-np.8.2.2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2037"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:pts-cs2.2.1"
msgid ""
"Aññātake aññātakasaññī pubbe appavārito gahapatikaṃ upasaṅkamitvā cīvare "
"vikappaṃ āpajjati, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"If the lay person is unrelated and the monk perceives them as unrelated, "
"and, without first being invited, he approaches them and specifies the kind "
"of robe he wants, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and "
"confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:pts-cs2.2.2"
msgid ""
"Aññātake vematiko pubbe appavārito gahapatikaṃ upasaṅkamitvā cīvare vikappaṃ "
"āpajjati, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"If the lay person is unrelated, but the monk is unsure if they are, and, "
"without first being invited, he approaches them and specifies the kind of "
"robe he wants, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:pts-cs2.2.3"
msgid ""
"Aññātake ñātakasaññī pubbe appavārito gahapatikaṃ upasaṅkamitvā cīvare "
"vikappaṃ āpajjati, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"If the lay person is unrelated, but the monk perceives them as related, and, "
"without first being invited, he approaches them and specifies the kind of "
"robe he wants, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="24"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2038"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:pts-cs2.2.4"
msgid "Ñātake aññātakasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If the lay person is related, but the monk perceives them as unrelated, he "
"commit an offense of wrong conduct."

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.57"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:pts-cs2.2.5"
msgid "Ñātake vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If the lay person is related, but the monk is unsure if they are, he commit "
"an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:pts-cs2.2.6"
msgid "Ñātake ñātakasaññī, anāpatti."
msgstr ""
"If the lay person is related and the monk perceives them as related, there "
"is no offense."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:pts-cs2.3.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="25"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-np.8.2.3"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2039"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:pts-cs2.3.1"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr "There is no offense:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:pts-cs2.3.2"
msgid "ñātakānaṃ,"
msgstr "if it is from relatives;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:pts-cs2.3.3"
msgid "pavāritānaṃ,"
msgstr "if it is from those who have given an invitation;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:pts-cs2.3.4"
msgid "aññassatthāya,"
msgstr "if it is for the benefit of another;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:pts-cs2.3.5"
msgid "attano dhanena,"
msgstr "if it is by means of his own property;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:pts-cs2.3.6"
msgid "mahagghaṃ cetāpetukāmassa appagghaṃ cetāpeti,"
msgstr ""
"if the lay person wishes to buy something expensive, but the monk gets them "
"to buy something inexpensive;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:pts-cs2.3.7"
msgid "ummattakassa,"
msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:pts-cs2.3.8"
msgid "ādikammikassāti."
msgstr "if he is the first offender."

#. </p><hr><p class="endsutta"><a class="sc" id="26"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2040"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np8:pts-cs2.3.9"
msgid "Upakkhaṭasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ aṭṭhamaṃ."
msgstr "The eighth rule, the training rule on what is set aside, is finished."

